00:03:03.300 --> 00:03:07.300
Glassblowers often work in groups known as shops.

00:03:07.300 --> 00:03:12.300
An apprentice dips a hollow blowpipe into the liquid glass.

00:03:12.300 --> 00:03:17.300
By twirling it, he gathers a blob of molten glass.

00:03:17.300 --> 00:03:22.300
He shapes the blob by rolling it on a smooth surface called a marver.

00:03:22.300 --> 00:03:26.300
He then passes the tube to the gaffer or shop master.

00:03:26.300 --> 00:03:30.300
He blows air into the tube and fashions the glass into a globe.

00:03:30.300 --> 00:03:39.300
Well, if a wine glass is being made, the tube is then passed to the stem maker, and another gather of glass is attached.

00:03:39.300 --> 00:03:45.300
It's then shaped by means of long pointed tongs to form the stem.

00:03:45.300 --> 00:03:49.300
Then another gather of hot glass is added to the stem.

00:03:49.300 --> 00:03:52.300
The craftsman rolls the tube on the arm of his chair.

00:03:52.300 --> 00:03:56.300
He forms the base of the glass.

